TI  - Climate finance as development aid
DO  - 10.4337/9781784715656.00009
AB  - In this chapter, we highlight the relevance of public climate finance - and notably ODA - for climate finance overall. The classification as ODA induces problems related to the normative justification of these financial flows as well as to obfuscation linked to the dual objectives of economic and social development on the one hand, and climate change mitigation and adaptation on the other hand. Since separate international goals exist for both, double counting of what is supposed to be new and additional climate finance should be avoided. Furthermore, confounding the goals creates incentives to spend mitigation finance inefficiently. In contrast, what is required is joint optimisation based on the recognition of distinct objectives as well as distinct instruments. Solutions require a separate accounting for climate finance within ODA, and the recognition that mitigation and climate finance goals are linked. Correspondingly, climate finance goals should be monitored more seriously at the international level. 
